Vice President Mike Pence visited Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Anchorage, Alaska to thank the members of the command for their service in providing missile defense for the United States. He emphasized the importance of missile defense in ensuring the safety and security of the American people. Pence also mentioned that the administration has secured an additional $5 billion in funding for missile defense and that there will be 20 new ground-based interceptors in Alaska. The administration will soon release a missile defense review to inform decisions about resources and training for the mission. Pence expressed gratitude to General Robinson and all the members of the command for their leadership and dedication in keeping America safe.